{"task":"forge-4d DENSE session, passes 9-16: WARRANT#22-30 shipped (SLS38->SLS45), SLS(43) crashed live -- ROOT CAUSE FOUND (Windows Application Hang, not silent crash)","totalSteps":16,"ts":"2026-07-14T09:46:53.8808763+02:00","detail":"MAJOR FINDING, 2026-07-14 09:23:22: terminal.exe (MT4 4.0.0.1470) was confirmed via Windows Event Log (Application log, Event ID 1002 'Application Hang') to have stopped responding to Windows and been force-closed, mid-calibration, during SLS(43)'s Phase 3B regime 2 (Strong Bear) global-random search (draw ~30000/50000). This is the FIRST time this project has ever gotten a named OS-level event for the terminal death -- prior sessions found no Application Error and speculated about memory pressure or coincident Windows Update/VSS activity. This time: no coincident RestartManager/VSS/System-log activity in the crash window (checked +-4min), current free memory was ~31% (not critically low post-crash). An 'Application Hang' (distinct from 'Application Error') means the process's message loop stopped responding to Windows for too long -- classic cause for an MT4 EA is a long synchronous compute loop (Phase 3B's 50,000-draw global-random search) that does not yield/pump messages often enough. This is now the leading hypothesis for ALL of this project's terminal deaths, not just this one, and is a concrete, fixable code issue (insert periodic yield/message-pump calls inside the long grid-search loops) rather than an external/environmental cause. NOT YET FIXED -- this pass only diagnosed it, via Get-WinEvent, did not yet patch the loop. A3's per-regime checkpoint (WARRANT#24, TW917_USDJPY_P5_P3BCKPT.dat, 1092 bytes, lastCompletedRegime=0) DID survive the hang and correctly preserved regime 1 (Strong Bull, 40.9% holdout) -- confirms A3 works exactly as designed: a resume of SLS(43) or any newer build would skip r1 and start at r2, not lose the whole run. Session also shipped, this pass, WARRANT#25 (Pre-Flight+Living-Edge scan, SLS40), #26 (triple-cell inversion alarm + phase table, SLS41), #27 (sign-agnostic bracket entries, gated off, SLS42), #28 (soft-membership Phase 3B fit, gated off, SLS43), #29 (Gate2 de-meaning + MFE/MAE bracket sizing, SLS44), #30 (always-on inversion-aware conviction trim, SLS45, built from Manuel's live description of 'systematic sign inversion' seen in the MT4 GUI Journal tab -- which this agent could never independently confirm via the log FILE because, we now know, the process was hung and force-killed before ever flushing its buffer to disk, not merely slow to flush as first assumed). SLS(45).ex4 sent to relay mailbox files/from-agent. forge_ledger.json has pass_9 through pass_16 fully documented. Five .mq4/.ex4 builds queued (SLS39-45), none has completed a run; SLS(43) is the one that hung. NEXT STEP, highest priority: (1) tell Manuel the terminal.exe process is gone (he may not know, if he was last looking at a frozen GUI window), (2) decide whether to resume SLS(43)/attach a newer build (A3 checkpoint makes this cheap now) or first patch the hang-inducing loop, (3) build the actual fix (yield periodically inside Phase 3B's global-random search and other long loops) as a new warrant if asked.","step":16}
